pr_body:
I'd like to return JSON error responses in the format of
```json
{
    "message": "Some error message"
}
```
instead of

```json
{
    "msg": "Some error message"
}
```

This PR allows that to be customized via the `JWT_ERROR_MESSAGE_KEY` configuration option.

Need tests.

As a sidenote, I tried the pipeline feature out with trackpy "in production" this weekend while addressing some reviewers' comments. I really like it. The raw video is so badly lit it's hard to see anything at all, so this usage is really nice:

```
@pims.pipeline
def preprocess(image):
    return pims.Frame(tp.bandpass(np.invert(image), 1, 11), frame_no=image.frame_no)
v = preprocess(raw_video)
```

This PR would simplify that to:

```
@pims.pipeline
def preprocess(image):
    return tp.bandpass(np.invert(image), 1, 11)
v = preprocess(raw_video)
```

def _rest_request(...) is appending a trailing slash to all URIs:
        if self.default_prefix in path and path[-1] != '/':
            path = path + '/'
        else:
            pass

but my read of the spec says that only needed for the root of the namespace '/redfish/v1/'. Change is to only append when default does not contain a trailing '/'.

Second part of fix for #499 which was lifted out of #500 

This has the issue that it changes the name of a large number of arrays but it seems like these should be setpoints per definition

